{{Han compound|手|alt1=扌|妾|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc}} – to receive (in the hand).

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsjap|t=to join, connect}}. Related to {{och-l|際|connection, border}}, as well as to {{cog|my|စပ်|t=to adjoin}} (STEDT).

STEDT also adduces another family, with similar phonetics and semantics, which however does not appear to be related:
* {{och-l|揖|to cluster together, crowd}}
* {{och-l|輯|to gather up, fold up, be crowded together}}
* {{och-l|集|to collect, come together, unite, accomplish}}
* {{och-l|雜|variegated, mixed}}

